WooCommerce provides native Model Context Protocol (MCP) support, which exposes store operations as discoverable tools for AI agents [1][2]. This integration uses the WordPress Abilities API and a shared WordPress MCP adapter to bridge AI clients with WooCommerce functionality [1][2].

To enable this, use the `mcp_integration` feature flag [1][2]. For external MCP servers, you can connect via a local proxy (like `@automattic/mcp-wordpress-remote`) to communicate with your WordPress installation [1][3][2].

Example configuration for an MCP client:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "woocommerce": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@automattic/mcp-wordpress-remote@latest"],
      "env": {
        "WP_API_URL": "https://yourstore.com/wp-json/woocommerce/mcp",
        "CUSTOM_HEADERS": "{\"X-MCP-API-Key\": \"key:secret\"}"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Several community-maintained MCP servers also exist [4][5][6], allowing you to interact with products, orders, and analytics through dedicated TypeScript-based tools [5][7].
